                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>
                           <material>Parchment, thick and low quality, arranged
                                        flesh-to-flesh and hair-to-hair with hair outermost, (<term type="disposition">FHHF</term>). ff. i-ii are in
                                        paper.</material>
                        </support>
                        <extent>
                           <seg part="N" type="object">
                              <objectType>Codex </objectType>
                           </seg>
                           <seg part="N" type="leaf">
                              <measure quantity="187" type="leaf">187</measure> + <measure quantity="2" type="endleaf">ii</measure>
                           </seg>, <seg part="N" type="dimensions">
                              <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                 <height quantity="138">138</height>
                                 <width max="94" min="86">86-94</width>
                              </dimensions>
                           </seg>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation> 1-187 + i-ii. Foliated in Arabic numerals, in pencil,
                                    recto, upper right.</foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p part="N">The manuscript consists of 24 quires: <list>
                                 <item>Quires 1-21<hi rend="superscript">8</hi>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="9r"> ff. 1-168</locus>
                                 </item>
                                 <item>Quire 22<hi rend="superscript">6</hi>
                                    ff. 169-174
                                 </item>
                                 <item>Quire 23<hi rend="superscript">6+2</hi>
                                    ff. 175-182, a bifolium is inserted
                                                after the first leaf</item>
                                 <item>Quire 24<hi rend="superscript">4+1</hi>
                                    ff. 183-187
                                 </item>
                              </list>
                           </p>
                           <signatures>
                              <p part="N">Signatures in Greek numerals in black ink on first
                                            rectos, upper outer corner, from quire 1, from αʹ to
                                            κγʹ: quire 3 is numbered as ββʹ.</p>
                              <p part="N">A modern signatures in Arabic numerals in pencil on first
                                            rectos, lower outer corner from quire 2.</p>
                           </signatures>
                        </collation>
                        <condition> The manuscript is fragile, there is some cockling,
                                    creasing, water staining and areas of dirt, in particula from f.
                                    129. Water staining at the tail towards the gutter has caused
                                    fading and blurring of text; text on ff. 66v, 71r, 187v is not
                                    legible. ff. 155, 157-159, 169, 170, 173, 174 have been repaired
                                    with Japanes paper.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" rulingMedium="hardpoint" writtenLines="16">
                                    written space <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
